sentences: Rob McCoury was born in York County, Pennsylvania on April 30, 1971.
In 1986 at the age of 15 he played bass with his Dad's band for the first time at a festival in Bath, NY.

His first show as a banjo player was in the spring of 1987 in Wilmington, DE at a benefit show for Ola Belle Reed, a singer/songwriter who penned one of his Dad's most requested songs, “High on the Mountain”, along with many others.
McCoury graduated from Susquehannock High School in 1989, and in 2009 he and his brother Ronnie both won the High School's Distinguished Alumni Award.
